comments.body:
The proposal from @kevinreiss and @mzelesky is not to use umlaut on the record page like we currently do. But to query solr on the isbn, issn and oclc and populate the 'Online Section' in the record page relying on the indexed information. 

We will index the records from the full dump using the information provided in the the 951 filed (electronic enrichment fields) and the 856.
As a start on this issue I will look into documenting `Document the umlaut functionality` #1034

comments.body: @faithc and @ccleeton since the FAQs/Help was not a part of the wireframes, and it appears that there's more content work to be done here, is this really MVP or not? I feel like this is being rushed. If it needs to happen for MVP, perhaps we should meet about this?

I think it's important to have a Help/Site info section with at least some content for the MVP, to be revised and enhanced as appropriate we move forward. (I think a good deal of content will be managed and generated by PS staff.) We do have some finalized content, such as the statement, which staff had initially requested be added to the current site in December 2019, so it would be great if this could be implemented. I'd be happy to meet to discuss.

@faithc no problem. I'll do this now, and we can revise as we go. 

However, you may need to rely on DRDS staff to update the Help/Site Info content, at least initially. One of the reasons we went with the WordPress API for the Help site in PULFA 2.0 is so that PS staff could have full control over the content.
